<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="1927" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[212,1172,1085,1308]" box="[212,329,1085,1109]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1927">
<heading box="[212,329,1085,1109]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="22" pageNumber="1927" reason="5">
<emphasis box="[212,329,1085,1109]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1927">Comments</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[212,1172,1085,1308]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1927">
Generally similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos et Aguiar" authorityYear="2014" box="[451,556,1125,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Loxopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="1927" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="duckei">
<emphasis box="[451,556,1125,1149]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1927">L. duckei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos &amp; Aguiar" authorityYear="2014" box="[618,716,1126,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Loxopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="1927" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenuis">
<emphasis box="[618,716,1126,1149]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1927">L. tenuis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it can be differentiated by having the gena almost entirely black (versus ventrally orange); subalar ridge moderately wide, elliptic (versus narrow, dash-like), and bright yellow (versus ferruginous or whitish). Further differentiated from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos &amp; Aguiar" authorityYear="2014" box="[660,756,1222,1245]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Loxopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="1927" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenuis">
<emphasis box="[660,756,1222,1245]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1927">L. tenuis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the anterior portion of T1 blackish (versus orange), and from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos et Aguiar" authorityYear="2014" box="[624,730,1253,1277]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Loxopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="1927" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="duckei">
<emphasis box="[624,730,1253,1277]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1927">L. duckei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the fore wing with distinct brownish spot (versus fore wing without spot).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
